he job's configured missed-run policy\" indicates the policy is retrieved (I/O)\n- If testing only the decision logic with a passed-in policy, this could be Unit. But the full behavior likely includes reading the policy from storage and potentially creating records in a database.\n- **Integration level** is the safe minimum. Test must set up job configuration, invoke the engine, and verify side effects (or at least that the configuration is correctly applied).\n\n---"}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":10,"cache_creation_input_tokens":13816,"cache_read_input_tokens":0,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":13816},"output_tokens":1,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"5f2e7fc6-7b26-4a5a-87f7-b6f911ad177c","uuid":"00413a1e-26ba-4625-9c2d-fab7cb426aa3"}
