all-back transitions handle the ambiguous hour correctly, and (3) UTC conversions are accurate. Test with actual 2024 or 2025 DST transition dates.","plan_consistent":true,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.15,"Integration":0.78,"System":0.05,"Agentic":0.01,"Workflow":0.01}},{"behavior_id":5,"description":"When a scheduled job's computed next run time has already passed (e.g., system was down), the engine determines whether to skip or backfill based on the job's configured missed-run policy.","minimum_level":"Integration","justification":"The phrase 'based on the job's configured missed-run policy' indicates the policy is read from storage (configuration, database, or job definition). A real failure includes: policy configuration is not read correctly, or the policy decision is not applied (backfill records not created). Testing the decision logic in isolation (Unit) would miss configuration I/O failures. Integration level is required to set up job configuration and verify the policy is applied correctly.","test_description":"Integration test that creates a job with a configured missed-run policy (e.g., MissedRunPolicy.BACKFILL), simulates a scenario where next_run_time has passed (e.g., next run at 10:00 AM but current time is 12:00 PM), invokes the engine's missed-run handler, and verifies the policy is applied: either no side effects occur (skip policy) or backfill records are created (backfill policy). Test both policy types.","plan_consistent":true,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.3,"Integration":0.6,"System":0.05,"Agentic":0.02,"Workflow":0.03}}]},"caller":{"type":"direct"}}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":10,"cache_creation_input_tokens":13816,"cache_read_input_tokens":0,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":13816},"output_tokens":1,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"5f2e7fc6-7b26-4a5a-87f7-b6f911ad177c"